subject: Scandinavian Nature Poetry (Late 19th century)
permalink: /Scandinavian Nature Poetry (Late 19th century)/Selma Lagerlöf/Selma Lagerlöf - Stories of the Land
---

In valleys deep, where echoes dwell,
Amidst the mountains high and grand,
I hear the stories nature tells,
In every whisper of the land.

The winding streams, like ribbons flow,
Connecting all that’s lost and found,
In every journey, we will go,
In nature’s arms, forever bound.


- Selma Lagerlöf
